frameDefinitions: A Process is finished and can no longer proceed.
A Process comes to an end.
Words in the frame refer to any Document that has a legal status or conventional social significance.

The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
Words in this frame describe the status of an Action with respect to a Code of laws or rules.
frameExamples: They got their marriage <t>licence</t> from Canada.
<t>Illegal</t> drug use is on the rise.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the name of the <fen>Process</fen> that occurs.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
Name of the event which occurs.
When the event ends.
Where the event takes place.
The holder of the document.
The authority that issues the document.
Obligation is the obligation that is imposed on the <fen>Bearer</fen> of the <fen>Document</fen>.
Right is the right of the <fen>Bearer</fen> of the <fen>Document</fen>  that is authorized by the <fen>Document</fen>.
Status is the state of the Bearer of the Document indicated by the Document.
Document is the piece of paper that has the legal status.
The action that the agent undertakes to achieve the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the agent attempts to achieve by performing the <fen>Means</fen> action.
An entity directed by the agent as part of the <fen>Means</fen> action in order to accomplish the <fen>Goal</fen>.
A participant function of an <fen>Instrument</fen> or <fen>Means</fen> in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails
The place where <fen>Means</fen> action succeeds or fails.
The <fen>Action</fen> is the behavior which complies with or violates the <fen>Code</fen>.
The <fen>Object</fen> complies with or violates the <fen>Code</fen> by virtue of its existence, location or possession.

They were all under subpoena <fex>to appear in court.</fex>
The couple just got their <fex>marriage</fex> certificate.
The police need a search <fex><t>warrant</t></fex> to enter his house.
